'''Justin C. Hamilton''' (born December 19, 1980) is an American-Belgian professional [[basketball]] [[shooting guard]]-[[point guard]] for [[Spirou Charleroi]] of the [[Basketball League Belgium]].<ref>http://www.sportando.com/en/europe/belgium/101029/justin-hamilton-will-get-a-belgian-passport-in-june.html</ref>  Hamilton played [[college basketball]] for the University of Florida, and then played professionally for several European teams. 

==High school==
A four-year starter at [[Booker High School (Sarasota, Florida)|Booker High School]] in Sarasota, Florida]], Hamilton was the state of Florida's class 4A player of the year as a senior in 1999.<ref>McGee, Brian Evers. "BOOKER'S HAMILTON NAMED STATE'S 4A PLAYER OF YEAR.(SPORTS)." Sarasota Herald Tribune. March 3, 1999.http://www.accessmylibrary.com/article-1G1-74053481/bookers-hamilton-named-states.html</ref>

==College==
Hamilton accepted an athletic scholarship to attend the [[University of Florida]], where he played for the [[Florida Gators men's basketball]] team under coach [[Billy Donovan]] from 1999 to 2003.<ref>Staff Reports. [http://www.accessmylibrary.com/article-1G1-74113646/hamilton-commits-florida-sports.html "Hamilton commits to Florida. (Sports)"] ''Sarasota Herald Tribune''. September 26, 1988.</ref>  He played a [[combo guard]] role for the Gators, and helped lead the team to four consecutive NCAA Tournament appearances.  The Gators reached the finals of the [[2000 NCAA Men's Division I Basketball Tournament]], before losing to [[1999-2000 Michigan State Spartans men's basketball team|Michigan State]] 76<U+2013>89.

==Pro career==
Went undrafted in the 2003 NBA draft.  Signed with the Detroit Pistons as a free agent.<ref>Dell, Alan."Booker's Hamilton heading to Pistons' camp.(SPORTS)." Sarasota Herald Tribune.September 23, 2003.http://www.accessmylibrary.com/coms2/summary_0286-24481478_ITM</ref> He was waived before the start of the season.  
Hamilton has been with  [[Spirou Charleroi]] of the [[Basketball League Belgium]] since 2007 where he helped lead the team to 5 Finals with 4 consecutive wins.<ref>http://belgacomspirou.sudinfo.be/team/justin-hamilton</ref>

==Belgian Nationality==
Hamilton received his Belgian Citizenship in June of 2013.<ref>http://www.sportando.com/en/europe/belgium/101029/justin-hamilton-will-get-a-belgian-passport-in-june.html</ref>
==Championships==
*Spanish ACB Champion 2005
*Belgium BLB Champion 2008, 2009, 2010, 2011

